modules.description: This module handles reading from and writing to tar archives using Unix file descriptors. It provides functions to extract files from and create tar archives, fold over archive entries, append files, and manipulate headers with support for filtering and custom headers. Concrete use cases include extracting specific files from a tar archive, creating a tar archive from a directory, and inspecting or modifying tar headers during archive processing.

This module handles reading from and writing to tar archives using Lwt_unix for asynchronous I/O. It provides functions to extract, create, and manipulate tar files, including operations for reading and writing headers, appending files, and folding over archive contents. Concrete use cases include asynchronously unpacking a tarball into a directory, building a tar archive from a directory tree, and inspecting or modifying individual headers during archive processing.
